WEBVTT

00:02.713 --> 00:05.466
Meredith: EVERY ACTION HAS
AN EQUAL AND OPPOSITE REACTION.

00:05.466 --> 00:08.179
EMERGENCY ROOMS
ARE KEPT IN BUSINESS

00:08.179 --> 00:10.391
BY PEOPLE WHO'VE LEARNED
THAT LESSON THE HARD WAY...

00:10.391 --> 00:13.304
DEREK: You made waffles
in our kitchen.

00:13.304 --> 00:15.266
[ Laughing ] NO, NOT ME --

00:15.266 --> 00:19.140
YOUR SISTER, IN BETWEEN WEEPY
PHONE CALLS WITH THE FIANCÃ©.

00:19.140 --> 00:21.102
...SKYDIVERS, BULL RIDERS --

00:21.102 --> 00:23.944
PEOPLE WHOSE BOLD IDEAS
CAN OFTEN RESULT

00:23.944 --> 00:26.277
IN BROKEN BONES
AND SMUSHED SPLEENS.

00:26.277 --> 00:28.149
Well, being away from home
is hard.

00:28.149 --> 00:30.411
I've been in D.C. for so long.
I know how she feels.

00:30.411 --> 00:31.612
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO BROUGHT HER HERE.

00:31.612 --> 00:32.743
SHE DOESN'T NEED
YOUR SYMPATHY.

00:32.743 --> 00:34.155
SHE NEEDS YOU
TO SEND HER HOME.

00:34.155 --> 00:35.366
Now, did she say that?

00:35.366 --> 00:37.208
I'M SURE SHE'S TELLING JAMES
ALL ABOUT

00:37.208 --> 00:38.659
HOW WE'RE
HOLDING HER HOSTAGE.

00:38.659 --> 00:40.621
Well, we can negotiate
the terms of her release

00:40.621 --> 00:43.003
when I get home
later tonight.
TONIGHT?

00:43.003 --> 00:44.255
YOU AND I
HAVE A SURGERY SCHEDULED

00:44.255 --> 00:45.586
THIS AFTERNOON TOGETHER.

00:45.586 --> 00:47.548
Another meeting popped up.

00:47.548 --> 00:49.260
I'm gonna
have Amy cover for me.

00:49.260 --> 00:51.302
MM!
Sorry.

00:51.302 --> 00:54.385
NO. NOT YOU.
THE WAFFLES ARE AMAZING.

00:54.385 --> 00:56.097
I'M GONNA MISS
HAVING A HOSTAGE.

00:56.097 --> 01:00.441
SURGEONS ARE TRAINED TO DEAL
WITH THE FALLOUT OF BOLD IDEAS.

01:00.441 --> 01:02.103
WE PICK UP THE PIECES

01:02.103 --> 01:04.185
AND DO OUR BEST
TO FIT THEM BACK TOGETHER.

01:04.185 --> 01:06.447
GUYS, JO'S DYING.

01:06.447 --> 01:08.489
THEY'RE STRESS HIVES.

01:08.489 --> 01:10.111
I'VE BEEN A MESS
SINCE I HEARD HUNT AND WEBBER

01:10.111 --> 01:11.612
TALK ABOUT FIRING
ONE OF US.

01:11.612 --> 01:13.994
YOU'RE A MESS? I'VE GAINED
EIGHT POUNDS THIS WEEK.

01:13.994 --> 01:15.496
YOU COULD STOP EATING.

01:15.496 --> 01:17.288
WHERE DO YOU EVEN GET THESE
AT 7:00 A.M.?

01:17.288 --> 01:19.120
DROP IT
BEFORE I DROP YOU.

01:19.120 --> 01:21.202
YOU KNOW WHO'S
NOT GETTING FIRED? ME.

01:21.202 --> 01:23.794
I'M GONNA KEEP MY HEAD DOWN
AND STAY OUT OF TROUBLE.

01:23.794 --> 01:25.336
NO, WE SHOULD BE
IMPRESSING THEM,

01:25.336 --> 01:27.338
SHOWING THEM THEY NEED US.
WAIT. I'M CONFUSED.

01:27.338 --> 01:29.470
SHOULD I KEEP MY HEAD DOWN,
OR SHOULD I PUT ON A SHOW?

01:29.470 --> 01:31.011
YOU JUST NEED TO GO
ONE WEEK

01:31.011 --> 01:32.803
WITHOUT HAVING
A NERVOUS BREAKDOWN.

01:32.803 --> 01:35.095
WHY DOES EVERYTHING
KEEP COMING BACK TO THAT?

01:35.095 --> 01:36.477
IT HAPPENED ONCE!

01:36.477 --> 01:38.599
RELAX. HEY, I'M THE ONE
WHO'S IN TROUBLE.

01:38.599 --> 01:40.641
LAST ONE IN,
FIRST ONE OUT.
OH, PLEASE.

01:40.641 --> 01:42.143
EVEN IF YOU WEREN'T
DR. BAILEY'S HUSBAND,

01:42.143 --> 01:43.484
YOU'RE STILL
WEBBER'S FAVORITE.

01:43.484 --> 01:45.486
OKAY, I NEED TWO OF YOU
FOR ROUNDS.

01:45.486 --> 01:47.358
WARREN, MURPHY,
LET'S GO.

01:47.358 --> 01:48.609
NICE KNOWING YOU.

01:52.363 --> 01:56.116
BRADEN MORRIS' ALC
AND T-CELL COUNTS ARE FANTASTIC.

01:56.116 --> 01:58.619
DO YOU THINK
IT MIGHT ACTUALLY BE TIME

01:58.619 --> 02:01.662
FOR THE BOY
TO COME OUT OF THE BUBBLE?
IT WOULD APPEAR SO.

02:01.662 --> 02:03.664
SO WHY DO YOU LOOK LIKE
I JUST PUNCHED A KITTEN?

02:03.664 --> 02:06.707
WE CAN'T SEND HIM HOME
UNTIL I TELL HIS PARENTS

02:06.707 --> 02:08.589
THE TRUTH
ABOUT HOW I TREATED HIM.

02:08.589 --> 02:11.422
AND BEFORE I DO THAT,
I NEED TO INFORM THE BOARD.

02:11.422 --> 02:13.464
Miranda: [ SIGHS ] YANG.
Cristina: MM?

02:13.464 --> 02:16.887
I GAVE A PATIENT
A STEM-CELL TRANSPLANT

02:16.887 --> 02:20.140
USING DEACTIVATED H.I.V.
AS A VIRAL VECTOR

02:20.140 --> 02:21.642
IN ORDER TO CURE HIS SCID.

02:21.642 --> 02:24.185
I DID SO
AGAINST HIS PARENTS' WISHES.

02:24.185 --> 02:26.527
WHOA.

02:27.728 --> 02:29.069
DID IT WORK?

02:29.069 --> 02:30.651
DAMN RIGHT, IT DID.

02:32.273 --> 02:34.445
UP TOP! HEY!

02:34.445 --> 02:35.776
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

02:35.776 --> 02:37.698
I'VE JUST
INFORMED THE BOARD.

02:37.698 --> 02:39.490
NOW,
LET'S GO SEE HIS FOLKS.

02:42.873 --> 02:45.666
OOH, LOOK AT
THIS CUTE, LITTLE FETUS.

02:45.666 --> 02:47.208
I WANT TO
SEND THIS TO MY MOM.

02:47.208 --> 02:49.250
OF COURSE, RIGHT AFTER
THE FIRST TRIMESTER --

02:49.250 --> 02:50.841
TWO MORE WEEKS.
COME ON, THAT'S SO FAR.

02:50.841 --> 02:53.173
LOOK, IF WE START
TELLING PEOPLE, WE
GOT TO TELL MY MOM.

02:53.173 --> 02:55.175
SHE ALREADY TRIED TO
TORPEDO OUR RELATIONSHIP ONCE

02:55.175 --> 02:56.427
OVER A HYPOTHETICAL CHILD.

02:56.427 --> 02:59.179
WHAT DO YOU THINK SHE'S GONNA DO
WITH A REAL ONE?

02:59.179 --> 03:00.641
OH. HEY, GUYS.

03:00.641 --> 03:03.103
HEY.
HI! HEY!

03:03.103 --> 03:06.687
JUST, UH, HAVING
A CHECKUP WITH OLD OB-GYN,

03:06.687 --> 03:09.230
MAKING SURE ALL THE PARTS
ARE...IN ORDER.

03:09.230 --> 03:10.901
YEAH.

03:10.901 --> 03:12.152
BOTH OF YOU?

03:12.152 --> 03:14.865
CALLIE TORRES?
HI. YES. THAT'S ME.

03:14.865 --> 03:16.777
UH, I THINK I CAN
HANDLE THIS ON MY OWN.

03:16.777 --> 03:18.739
OKAY. [ CHUCKLES ]

03:18.739 --> 03:21.201
[ LAUGHS ]
THAT WAS TERRIBLE!

03:21.201 --> 03:23.494
AND WHAT'S UP WITH THIS?
I DON'T KNOW!

03:23.494 --> 03:24.955
MMM!
HEY!

03:24.955 --> 03:26.247
THE, UH,
FIRST CANDIDATE'S HERE

03:26.247 --> 03:27.207
AND WAITING
IN THE CONFERENCE ROOM.

03:27.207 --> 03:29.880
MM. I'M ON MY WAY NOW.
OKAY.

03:29.880 --> 03:31.252
SO, I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE

03:31.252 --> 03:33.254
HE'S MAKING YOU
PICK YOUR REPLACEMENT.

03:33.254 --> 03:35.296
[ Muffled ] MM.

03:35.296 --> 03:38.218
I'M INTERVIEWING DR. RUSSELL'S
REPLACEMENT, NOT MINE --

03:38.218 --> 03:40.140
WHICH I VOLUNTEERED TO DO,
BY THE WAY.

03:40.140 --> 03:41.602
IT'S A PUNISHMENT.

03:41.602 --> 03:44.765
IT'S LIKE MAKING YOU CLEAN
THE APARTMENT YOU'RE VACATING.

03:44.765 --> 03:46.397
NO, OWEN KNOWS
THIS IS THE RIGHT MOVE FOR ME.

03:46.397 --> 03:48.269
HE'S BEEN
NOTHING BUT SUPPORTIVE.
MNH-MNH.

03:48.269 --> 03:51.352
SOMETHING'S COMING.
I CAN FEEL IT IN MY BONES.

03:55.195 --> 03:57.448
EW.
I HATE HIS FACE.

03:57.448 --> 03:58.989
OKAY,
NOW LOOK ME IN THE EYE

03:58.989 --> 04:01.822
AND TELL ME
THIS ISN'T A PUNISHMENT.

04:01.822 --> 04:03.784
THANK YOU
FOR THIS WAFFLE.

04:03.784 --> 04:05.456
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:05.456 --> 04:07.418
ALL RIGHT, MS. CAMPBELL.
I'M JUST GONNA GRAB YOU
SOME GAUZE AND --

04:07.418 --> 04:09.079
NON-ADHERENT GAUZE,
DR. KEPNER.

04:09.079 --> 04:10.331
DO YOU PREFER
TAPE OR COBAN?

04:10.331 --> 04:11.582
WHERE DID YOU COME FROM?

04:11.582 --> 04:13.334
OH, JUST TRYING TO
BE USEFUL, PROACTIVE.

04:13.334 --> 04:14.875
FINDING NEEDS
AND FILLING THEM --

04:14.875 --> 04:16.086
THAT'S MY BUSINESS.

04:16.086 --> 04:19.009
30-YEAR-OLD MALE,
MOTORCYCLE VERSUS S.U.V.

04:19.009 --> 04:21.642
COMPLEX SCALP LAC
AND BILATERAL HIP DISLOCATIONS.

04:21.642 --> 04:23.263
VITALS ARE STABLE.

04:23.263 --> 04:25.646
WILSON,
YOU WANT TO BE USEFUL?

04:25.646 --> 04:26.727
YEAH.
TAKE HIM TO TRAUMA ONE.

04:26.727 --> 04:28.439
START THE ABCs,
GET HIM OFF THE BOARD,

04:28.439 --> 04:29.600
AND GET HIM
HIS TRAUMA X-RAYS.

04:29.600 --> 04:31.442
AND I WILL JOIN YOU
AS SOON AS I FINISH UP

04:31.442 --> 04:32.653
WITH MS. CAMPBELL
OVER THERE.

04:32.653 --> 04:34.234
ABSOLUTELY.
OF COURSE, DR. KEPNER.

04:34.234 --> 04:35.566
THANK YOU
FOR THE OPPORTUNITY.

04:35.566 --> 04:37.528
YOU'RE WELCOME!

04:39.109 --> 04:41.452
Teresa: [ Laughing ]
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

04:41.452 --> 04:44.244
WE CAN TAKE HIM HOME?
ABSOLUTELY.

04:44.244 --> 04:45.456
[ SIGHS ]
OH!

04:45.456 --> 04:48.208
THIS IS JUST --
THIS IS JUST WONDERFUL.

04:48.208 --> 04:49.870
THANK YOU, DR. BAILEY.

04:49.870 --> 04:51.622
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR HEARING US

04:51.622 --> 04:54.214
AND JUST LETTING HIM
GET BETTER ON HIS OWN.

04:56.046 --> 04:58.839
UH, MR. MORRIS...

04:58.839 --> 05:02.302
BRADEN DID NOT
GET BETTER ON HIS OWN.

05:02.302 --> 05:04.635
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

05:04.635 --> 05:07.017
I GAVE HIM
THE TREATMENT.

05:07.017 --> 05:11.141
THEY DID NOT REACT
AS I HAD HOPED THEY WOULD.

05:11.141 --> 05:13.644
[ SIGHS ] LEGAL ACTION
NEVER CROSSED YOUR MIND?

05:13.644 --> 05:17.107
I HAD HOPED THAT THEY WOULD
SEE THE BIGGER PICTURE.

05:17.107 --> 05:19.740
UH, DR. EDWARDS
SHOULD BE EXCUSED.

05:19.740 --> 05:20.821
SHE WASN'T INVOLVED.

05:20.821 --> 05:22.072
DID SHE KNOW
WHAT YOU WERE DOING

05:22.072 --> 05:23.944
AND FAIL TO REPORT IT?

05:27.788 --> 05:29.410
SHE WAS INVOLVED.

05:29.410 --> 05:31.372
OKAY, UM...

05:31.372 --> 05:33.293
I'M GONNA GET SOMEONE
ON THE PHONE FROM LEGAL,

05:33.293 --> 05:36.216
AND TILL I COME BACK,
DON'T GO ANYWHERE.

05:36.216 --> 05:38.959
DON'T SPEAK TO ANYONE.
DON'T MOVE.

05:38.959 --> 05:40.881
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

05:40.881 --> 05:42.302
[ SIGHS ]

05:42.302 --> 05:44.304
OKAY.

05:53.774 --> 05:55.856
PARENTS
AUTHORIZED YOUR TREATMENT

05:55.856 --> 05:57.438
WITH SIGNED CONSENT.
YES.

05:57.438 --> 06:00.821
THEN THEY TOLD DR. EDWARDS
THAT THEY CHANGED THEIR MIND.

06:00.821 --> 06:02.362
YES.

06:02.362 --> 06:05.115
DR. EDWARDS INFORMED YOU,
DR. BAILEY,

06:05.115 --> 06:07.077
OF THE PARENTS'
WITHDRAWAL OF CONSENT.

06:07.077 --> 06:08.248
YES.
YES.

06:08.248 --> 06:09.990
AND THEN
YOU GAVE THE PATIENT

06:09.990 --> 06:11.952
THE STEM-CELL TRANSPLANT
ANYWAY.

06:13.754 --> 06:15.796
HAVE YOU TOLD ANYONE ELSE
ABOUT THIS?

06:15.796 --> 06:18.168
I INFORMED DR. YANG
THIS MORNING

06:18.168 --> 06:19.800
AS A REPRESENTATIVE
OF THE BOARD.

06:19.800 --> 06:20.921
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

06:20.921 --> 06:22.713
SHE GAVE ME A HIGH-FIVE.

06:24.054 --> 06:25.596
AND DID YOU APOLOGIZE?

06:25.596 --> 06:26.967
TO DR. YANG?

06:26.967 --> 06:28.809
TO THE PARENTS.

06:28.809 --> 06:31.932
AN APOLOGY COULD GO A LONG WAY
IN CIRCUMSTANCES LIKE THIS.

06:31.932 --> 06:34.394
AN APOLOGY
IS ONLY EFFECTIVE

06:34.394 --> 06:36.066
WHEN
A MISTAKE'S BEEN MADE.

06:36.066 --> 06:38.859
I CHOSE
NOT TO HONOR THEIR WISHES.

06:38.859 --> 06:39.980
IT WASN'T A MISTAKE.

06:41.942 --> 06:44.825
[ SIGHS ]

06:44.825 --> 06:46.697
ALL RIGHT, DR. ROSS.

06:46.697 --> 06:48.789
TELL US WHAT'S SO SPECIAL
ABOUT LITTLE JACOB HERE.

06:48.789 --> 06:50.701
JACOB HAS
AN OMPHALOCELE.

06:50.701 --> 06:53.083
HE WAS BORN WITH HIS ABDOMINAL
ORGANS OUTSIDE OF HIS BODY.

06:53.083 --> 06:56.537
WE'VE BEEN MANAGING HIM
WITH DAILY APPLICATION OF
SILVER-SULFADIAZINE OINTMENT

06:56.537 --> 06:58.959
AS A BRIDGE
TO DELAYED CLOSURE.
AND THAT'S YOUR JOB.

06:58.959 --> 07:01.001
AND TO KEEP AN EYE
ON THE OTHER TINY HUMANS.

07:01.001 --> 07:02.543
IT SHOULD BE
A QUIET AND ADORABLE DAY.

07:04.344 --> 07:05.676
WHOA.

07:05.676 --> 07:07.678
LOOK AT YOU, ALL GROWN UP.

07:07.678 --> 07:09.640
HOW'S THE PRIVATE SECTOR?
OH, COULDN'T BE BETTER.

07:09.640 --> 07:12.723
I, UH, JUST CAME BY TO CHECK ON
MY INGUINAL-HERNIA KID.

07:12.723 --> 07:15.015
OH. OH, GREAT.
WELL, DON'T BE A STRANGER.

07:15.015 --> 07:16.897
YEAH, YOU TOO.

07:16.897 --> 07:18.729
HEY, ROSS, HOLD UP.

07:18.729 --> 07:20.400
I'M NOT GONNA HIT YOU.

07:20.400 --> 07:22.863
I JUST, UH, WANT YOU
TO CHECK UP ON AN OLD
PATIENT OF MINE --

07:22.863 --> 07:24.735
KEVIN PLATT,
SHORT-GUT KID.

07:24.735 --> 07:26.737
DID HE GET
HIS S.T.E.P. PROCEDURE YET?

07:26.737 --> 07:28.739
ROBBINS HAS IT SCHEDULED
FOR WEDNESDAY.

07:28.739 --> 07:31.031
HE'S HERE FOR TPN
TILL THEN.

07:31.031 --> 07:32.833
COOL. GOT IT.

07:34.575 --> 07:36.076
THAT'S MY TABLET.

07:36.076 --> 07:38.879
MONICA ZARR, 27,
IN REMISSION FROM RECTAL CANCER.

07:38.879 --> 07:40.921
[ FARTS ]

07:40.921 --> 07:42.292
OKAY.

07:42.292 --> 07:44.845
UH, MONICA NOW SUFFERS
FROM POOR SPHINCTER CONTROL

07:44.845 --> 07:46.637
DUE TO HER
LOW ANTERIOR RESECTION.
[ FARTS ]

07:46.637 --> 07:48.298
SHE'S HERE TODAY
FOR THE IMPLANTATION

07:48.298 --> 07:50.260
OF THE PERMANENT
RECTAL PACEMAKER.

07:50.260 --> 07:53.223
GOSH, WHEN YOU SAY IT,
IT SOUNDS SO SEXY.

07:53.223 --> 07:54.805
[ FARTING ]

07:55.806 --> 07:57.017
SORRY.

07:57.017 --> 07:58.769
HONEY, THERE'S
NO NEED TO APOLOGIZE.

07:58.769 --> 08:00.360
[ FARTING CONTINUES ]
THEY'RE DOCTORS.

08:00.360 --> 08:02.943
UM, MONICA,
I ASKED YOU TO KEEP RECORDS

08:02.943 --> 08:04.735
OF YOUR MOVEMENTS
AFTER YOUR LAST SURGERY.

08:04.735 --> 08:07.157
RIGHT. THE LOG LOG.

08:07.157 --> 08:09.910
PAUL, GIVE HIM
THE POOP DIARY.
SURE.

08:09.910 --> 08:12.573
EVERY 4 HOURS
AND 26 MINUTES.

08:12.573 --> 08:14.995
[ FARTING CONTINUES ]

08:14.995 --> 08:17.668
THE SACRAL-NERVE-STIMULATOR LEAD
WE IMPLANTED

08:17.668 --> 08:20.210
SHOULD HAVE CUT YOUR
FREQUENCIES DOWN FAR BELOW THIS.

08:20.210 --> 08:23.924
I'M SORRY. I'M GONNA
RECOMMEND THAT WE NOT IMPLANT
THE PERMANENT PACEMAKER.

08:23.924 --> 08:26.386
IN FACT, I THINK
WE SHOULD USE THE O.R. TIME

08:26.386 --> 08:29.129
TO REMOVE THE LEAD WIRE.
BUT I'M POOPING WAY LESS.

08:29.129 --> 08:31.552
BUT IT'S NOT ENOUGH TO CONSIDER
THE DEVICE EFFECTIVE.

08:31.552 --> 08:35.055
WE SHOULD
EXPLORE SOME OTHER OPTIONS.
SUCH AS?

08:35.055 --> 08:38.729
ANTIDIARRHEALS,
HIGH-FIBER DIET, SMALLER MEALS.

08:38.729 --> 08:40.561
I'M A PROFESSIONAL DANCER.

08:40.561 --> 08:43.273
MY DIET'S PRETTY MUCH
LEAVES AND TWIGS ALREADY.

08:43.273 --> 08:45.315
THERE HAS TO BE
SOMETHING ELSE.

08:45.315 --> 08:47.738
SWEETIE, WE MADE IT THROUGH
YOUR CANCER.

08:47.738 --> 08:50.070
WE'LL MAKE IT THROUGH THIS.
[ BELCHES ]

08:51.411 --> 08:52.953
I AM SO SORRY.
I COULDN'T HELP IT.

08:52.953 --> 08:55.786
BUT ALSO, SHE FARTED
LIKE 80 TIMES, AND I
DID NOT LAUGH ONCE.

08:55.786 --> 08:57.748
NO, YOU JUST BELCHED
TO RATTLE THE WINDOWS.

08:57.748 --> 08:59.790
AND DR. WARREN
DID NEITHER,

08:59.790 --> 09:01.582
SO HE'S GONNA
TAKE THE LEAD ON THE LAP CHOLE.

09:01.582 --> 09:03.333
YOU PREP MONICA
FOR SURGERY.
YES, SIR.

09:03.333 --> 09:05.966
AND TAKE AN ANTACID
BEFORE YOU GO BACK IN THERE.

09:11.592 --> 09:13.974
NO, YOU NEED TO
BEND THE KNEE FIRST.

09:13.974 --> 09:15.435
DID YOU GET THOSE X-RAYS,
WILSON?

09:15.435 --> 09:17.808
[ SCOFFS ] THINK I'D BE IN HERE
IF SHE HADN'T?

09:17.808 --> 09:20.601
WELL, SOMEBODY'S
SURE A GRUMPUS TODAY.

09:20.601 --> 09:21.772
WILSON, FILL ME IN.

09:21.772 --> 09:23.894
HEY, WHAT THE HELL?

09:23.894 --> 09:26.236
I'LL BE WITH YOU IN
TWO SHAKES OF A LAMB'S
TAIL, DR. TORRES.

09:26.236 --> 09:28.949
VITALS HAVE BEEN STABLE.
TRAUMA LAB'S DONE.

09:28.949 --> 09:31.952
PRIMARY SURVEY REVEALED A LARGE,
BRISKLY BLEEDING SCALP LAC.

09:31.952 --> 09:33.784
I PUT A PRESSURE DRESSING ON
FOR YOU TO ASSESS.

09:33.784 --> 09:36.787
C.T. NEGATIVE FOR ABDOMINAL
OR INTRACRANIAL HEMORRHAGE,

09:36.787 --> 09:38.959
BUT DID SHOW
BILATERAL HIP DISLOCATIONS,

09:38.959 --> 09:40.871
ONE ANTERIOR
AND ONE POSTERIOR,

09:40.871 --> 09:43.704
WITH AN ACETABULAR
WALL FRACTURE, BUT
BOTH HAVE BEEN REDUCED.

09:43.704 --> 09:45.966
WILSON, THIS TRACTION
PIN'S NOT GONNA PLACE
ITSELF. LET'S GO.

09:45.966 --> 09:47.087
OH, YES. SURE.
OF COURSE.

09:47.087 --> 09:48.969
SUCH A GRUMPUS!

09:48.969 --> 09:51.381
DO YOU SEE THIS PIN,
KEPNER?

09:51.381 --> 09:53.974
YOU CALL ME THAT NONSENSE WORD
ONE MORE TIME,

09:53.974 --> 09:55.806
YOU WON'T LIKE
WHERE I STICK IT.

09:55.806 --> 09:57.517
[ DRILL WHIRS ]

10:01.852 --> 10:05.105
SO, YOU'LL ACCESS THE SPINE
THROUGH THE RETROPERITONEUM,

10:05.105 --> 10:07.818
AND I WILL PERFORM
THE FUSION WITH BONE GRAFT

10:07.818 --> 10:09.109
BETWEEN L5 AND S1.

10:09.109 --> 10:10.440
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

10:10.440 --> 10:11.822
DO YOU NEED TO TAKE THAT?

10:11.822 --> 10:13.403
[ CLEARS THROAT, SIGHS ]

10:13.403 --> 10:14.695
NOPE.

10:14.695 --> 10:16.076
SO, DEREK USUALLY
DOES THE --

10:16.076 --> 10:18.038
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

10:18.038 --> 10:20.040
YOU CAN TAKE THE CALL.
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S FINE.

10:20.040 --> 10:21.832
[ SIGHS ] I'M SORRY.

10:21.832 --> 10:25.045
JUST BECAUSE DEREK AND
I ARE HAVING A HARD TIME
JUGGLING OUR LIVES,

10:25.045 --> 10:26.667
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THAT WE SHOULD KEEP
YOU FROM YOURS.

10:26.667 --> 10:28.088
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I LIKED YOU A LOT BETTER

10:28.088 --> 10:29.960
WHEN YOU WERE THE SISTER-IN-LAW
WHO DIDN'T GIVE A CRAP.

10:29.960 --> 10:32.462
COULD WE JUST GO BACK TO THAT?
THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

10:33.633 --> 10:36.386
AM I QUALIFIED
TO RUN THE DEPARTMENT?

10:36.386 --> 10:38.098
YIKES.
YOU KNOW, NOT MY CALL.

10:38.098 --> 10:40.640
WHAT I DO KNOW IS THAT
FOR SOME STRANGE REASON,

10:40.640 --> 10:42.853
SINCE I WAS A RESIDENT,
I KEEP GETTING THROWN

10:42.853 --> 10:45.816
THE RISKIEST, HIGH-PROFILE
CARDIOTHORACIC SURGERIES.

10:45.816 --> 10:49.109
I MEAN, WHY ME, YOU KNOW?
UH-HUH.

10:49.109 --> 10:52.322
SO, YOU DID YOUR FELLOWSHIP

10:52.322 --> 10:54.444
IN PHILADELPHIA
UNDER JACK ALEXANDER?

10:54.444 --> 10:55.986
OH, DO YOU KNOW
DR. ALEXANDER?
MM-HMM.

10:55.986 --> 10:58.829
OH, SUCH A GREAT GUY.
REALLY, SWEET AS PIE.

10:58.829 --> 11:02.242
WHICH IS WHY IT WAS ALWAYS
A LITTLE EMBARRASSING

11:02.242 --> 11:04.624
WHEN OUR CHIEF OF SURGERY
WOULD COME TO ME FOR CONSULTS

11:04.624 --> 11:06.086
INSTEAD OF DR. ALEXANDER.

11:06.086 --> 11:09.289
I TOOK IT AS A COMPLIMENT,
BUT STILL, AWKWARD.

11:09.289 --> 11:11.001
MM.

11:14.214 --> 11:16.176
KNOCK, KNOCK.
WHO'S THERE?

11:16.176 --> 11:18.719
INTERRUPTING JELLYFISH.
INTERRUPTING JE--

11:18.719 --> 11:20.851
OHH!
THAT'S MY FAVORITE ONE!

11:20.851 --> 11:22.602
HEY, DR. ROSS.

11:22.602 --> 11:24.434
KEVIN DOESN'T NEED THE TPN
THIS AFTERNOON.

11:24.434 --> 11:26.807
DR. KAREV SAID HE COULD
DO HIS SURGERY TODAY.

11:26.807 --> 11:29.479
OH, THAT'S --
BUT DR. ROBBINS.

11:29.479 --> 11:33.573
ROSS, LET ME EXPLAIN
SHORT-BOWEL SYNDROME TO YOU.

11:33.573 --> 11:36.656
KEVIN HERE IS MISSING
A BIG CHUNK OF HIS SMALL BOWEL,

11:36.656 --> 11:38.909
WHICH MEANS HE NEEDS SURGERY
TO LENGTHEN IT.

11:38.909 --> 11:41.121
THE SOONER WE OPERATE,
THE SOONER HE GOES HOME.

11:41.121 --> 11:43.163
SOUND GOOD TO YOU?
YEAH.

11:43.163 --> 11:45.325
WE JUST NEED TO TRANSFER YOU
ONTO MY SERVICE.

11:45.325 --> 11:47.828
DR. ROSS WILL PICK UP
THE PAPERWORK FOR YOU.

11:51.131 --> 11:53.794
HEY, I SHOULD LET
DR. ROBBINS KNOW.

11:53.794 --> 11:55.545
HE'S MY PATIENT.

11:55.545 --> 11:57.758
OR HE WILL BE, AS SOON AS
THEY SIGN THE TRANSFER PAPERS.

11:57.758 --> 11:59.219
I DON'T FEEL GOOD
ABOUT THIS.

11:59.219 --> 12:00.891
YOU GOT TWO CHOICES.

12:00.891 --> 12:02.552
YOU CAN FEEL GOOD ABOUT IT
AND SCRUB IN WITH ME,

12:02.552 --> 12:04.394
OR YOU CAN
RAT ME OUT TO ROBBINS

12:04.394 --> 12:06.436
AND I TELL HER YOU
DIDN'T CHECK PLACEMENT OF
SOME KID'S FEEDING TUBE

12:06.436 --> 12:08.228
AND HE NEARLY DIED
FROM ASPIRATION PNEUMONIA.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.349
BUT THAT'S NOT TRUE.

12:09.349 --> 12:10.730
YEAH, BUT I WORKED WITH HER
FOR YEARS.

12:10.730 --> 12:12.652
YOU WENT NUTS
AND KILLED MY DAD.

12:12.652 --> 12:14.734
WHO'S SHE GONNA BELIEVE?

12:23.413 --> 12:24.574
YOU'VE ALREADY BEEN
THE HEAD OF YOUR OWN DEPARTMENT

12:24.574 --> 12:25.916
FOR TWO YEARS.

12:25.916 --> 12:27.958
YOU THINK
I LOOK TOO YOUNG.

12:27.958 --> 12:30.210
I FINISHED HIGH SCHOOL
EARLY.

12:30.210 --> 12:31.792
ALSO MED SCHOOL.

12:31.792 --> 12:33.834
IT'S PRETTY ANNOYING, RIGHT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:33.834 --> 12:35.585
YEAH,
IT'S PRETTY ANNOYING.

12:36.716 --> 12:38.508
EXCUSE ME.
SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

12:38.508 --> 12:41.181
CAN I BORROW DR. YANG
FOR A MOMENT?

12:41.181 --> 12:42.432
EXCUSE ME.

12:44.644 --> 12:47.978
HOPE YOU SAVED THE BIG GUNS
FOR LAST.

12:47.978 --> 12:50.230
THEY'RE ALL SOLID CANDIDATES
ON PAPER,

12:50.230 --> 12:51.521
BUT BETWEEN
THE HUMBLE-BRAGGER

12:51.521 --> 12:53.153
AND THE GIRL WHO RODE IN
ON THE BIG WHEEL --

12:53.153 --> 12:54.694
CRISTINA, I NEED TO KNOW

12:54.694 --> 12:56.526
EXACTLY WHAT BAILEY SAID TO YOU
THIS MORNING.

12:56.526 --> 12:58.108
[ SIGHS ] ABOUT?

12:58.108 --> 12:59.779
HER PATIENT --
THE DEACTIVATED H.I.V.

12:59.779 --> 13:02.202
DRAWING A BLANK.

13:02.202 --> 13:03.283
REALLY?

13:03.283 --> 13:05.115
WELL, I'VE BEEN
INTERVIEWING ALL DAY.

13:05.115 --> 13:06.786
I'M SURPRISED
I REMEMBER MY OWN NAME.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.999
YOU KNOW WHAT?
IT'S PROBABLY FOR THE BEST.

13:08.999 --> 13:11.751
OH, AND...
GO EASY ON THESE GUYS.

13:11.751 --> 13:14.414
YOU KNOW,
THEY CAN'T ALL BE YOU.

13:16.416 --> 13:19.299
DR. AVERY, I HAVEN'T
HELD MY SON IN MONTHS,

13:19.299 --> 13:21.631
AND I WANT HIM TO COME OUT,
BUT FOR ALL WE KNOW,

13:21.631 --> 13:23.513
SHE COULD BE MAKING UP NUMBERS
TO COVER HER OWN ASS.

13:23.513 --> 13:25.926
YEAH, WE CAN'T TRUST
THAT IT'S SAFE.

13:25.926 --> 13:27.807
I MEAN, WHAT IF WE GET HIM HOME
AND SOMETHING HAPPENS?

13:27.807 --> 13:29.930
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I UNDERSTAND YOUR CONCERNS.

13:29.930 --> 13:31.691
WHAT I'M SAYING IS
IF THE LABS SHOW --

13:31.691 --> 13:33.693
ARE YOU A PARENT,
DR. AVERY?

13:39.279 --> 13:43.243
MY, UM -- MY WIFE AND I
ARE, UH, EXPECTING.

13:43.243 --> 13:47.077
WELL, IF SOMEONE
DID THIS TO YOU, YOUR CHILD,

13:47.077 --> 13:48.708
HOW WOULD YOU REACT?

13:51.411 --> 13:53.954
I'LL GO AHEAD AND RUN
SOME NEW LABS FOR YOU MYSELF.

13:53.954 --> 13:55.665
[ SIGHS ]

13:59.339 --> 14:01.221
ALL RIGHT,
THAT MIGHT BE ENOUGH WEIGHT.

14:01.221 --> 14:02.762
ALL RIGHT.
READY FOR THAT X-RAY?

14:02.762 --> 14:05.175
Man: RIGHT AWAY.
WHOOPS! LOOKS LIKE
I NEED MORE IRRIGATION.

14:05.175 --> 14:06.226
UH, WILSON,
CAN YOU TAKE OVER?

14:06.226 --> 14:08.098
YES, ABSOLUTELY,
DR. KEPNER.

14:11.391 --> 14:13.853
[ Mockingly ]
"ABSOLUTELY DR. KEPNER."

14:13.853 --> 14:16.026
[ Normal voice ] WHO ARE YOU?
I THOUGHT YOU HAD GRIT.

14:16.026 --> 14:18.238
I DO! I DO HAVE GRIT!

14:18.238 --> 14:20.610
OKAY, WELL, ALL I SEE
IS SOME "YES, MA'AM,
NO, MA'AM" SISSY GIRL,

14:20.610 --> 14:22.242
AND THERE'S NO PLACE IN ORTHO
FOR SISSY GIRLS.

14:22.242 --> 14:24.034
DO YOU HEAR ME?

14:24.034 --> 14:26.116
CHECK YOURSELF
BEFORE YOU WRECK YOURSELF.

14:28.078 --> 14:29.329
SWEETIE, LOOK.

14:29.329 --> 14:32.372
THIS SAYS YOGA MIGHT HELP.
YOU LOVE YOGA.

14:32.372 --> 14:36.256
ARE YOU CRAZY?
I CAN'T DO DOWNWARD DOG.

14:36.256 --> 14:37.547
IN A HOT ROOM?

14:37.547 --> 14:39.459
[ FARTS ]
[ GROANS ]

14:39.459 --> 14:41.421
[ SIGHS ]

14:41.421 --> 14:44.594
A BUNCH OF YOGA
WON'T GET ME MY JOB BACK.

14:44.594 --> 14:47.097
YOU LOST YOUR JOB
OVER THIS?

14:47.097 --> 14:50.270
THEY CAN'T FIRE YOU OVER
SOMETHING YOU CAN'T CONTROL.

14:50.270 --> 14:52.222
AFTER THE CANCER,

14:52.222 --> 14:55.355
I WAS SUPPOSED TO HAVE
MY BIG RETURN TO THE STAGE.

14:55.355 --> 14:57.277
I WAS ABLE TO MAKE IT
THROUGH REHEARSALS,

14:57.277 --> 14:58.898
RUNNING BACK AND FORTH
TO THE BATHROOM,

14:58.898 --> 15:01.281
BUT THEN, THE FIRST
FULL RUN-THROUGH,

15:01.281 --> 15:03.903
NO BREAKS...

15:03.903 --> 15:05.155
OH, NO.

15:05.155 --> 15:08.408
...BLASTOFF, IN THE MIDDLE
OF A PIROUETTE.

15:08.408 --> 15:10.410
THE FACT THAT IT DIDN'T HAPPEN
IN FRONT OF AN AUDIENCE

15:10.410 --> 15:13.833
IS THE ONLY THING THAT
KEPT ME FROM SHOOTING
MYSELF IN THE FACE.

15:13.833 --> 15:15.625
SHE'S EXAGGERATING.

15:15.625 --> 15:18.748
PAUL, IT WAS LIKE
FRICKIN' SPIN ART.

15:20.420 --> 15:21.801
[ SIGHS ]

15:26.506 --> 15:28.008
HEY, WHERE'S KEVIN PLATT?

15:28.008 --> 15:29.759
DR. KAREV
TOOK HIM UP TO SURGERY.

15:29.759 --> 15:32.852
HEY, WHAT, ARE YOU
POACHING PATIENTS NOW?
I DIDN'T POACH ANYTHING.

15:32.852 --> 15:34.854
YOU STOLE
MY SHORT-GUT KID.
[ SIGHS ] ALL RIGHT.

15:34.854 --> 15:37.107
UP UNTIL A FEW WEEKS AGO,
HE WAS OUR SHORT-GUT KID.

15:37.107 --> 15:39.269
LOOK, HIS PARENTS KNOW ME.
THEY'RE FINE WITH THIS.

15:39.269 --> 15:42.522
CONSENTS ARE SIGNED,
AND HE'S JUST ABOUT...PREPPED.

15:42.522 --> 15:43.863
ROSS?

15:43.863 --> 15:45.525
REALLY? [ SCOFFS ]

15:47.067 --> 15:49.069
THE KID'S
ON THE OPERATING TABLE.

15:49.069 --> 15:51.071
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO?

15:51.071 --> 15:53.413
THIS WAS A JERK-ASS MOVE,
KAREV,

15:53.413 --> 15:55.705
AND YOU KNOW IT.

15:58.248 --> 15:59.579
SO, NO ONE'S QUALIFIED?

15:59.579 --> 16:02.212
NO, I MEAN,
THEY'RE ALL QUALIFIED...

16:02.212 --> 16:03.923
BUT OWEN'S RIGHT.

16:03.923 --> 16:06.756
I NEED TO ACCEPT THAT
NONE OF THEM ARE GONNA BE ME.

16:06.756 --> 16:09.219
THAT'S HIS PLAN.
WHAT'S HIS PLAN?

16:09.219 --> 16:11.261
OWEN.
DIDN'T MAKE SENSE BEFORE.

16:11.261 --> 16:13.593
A FELLOW INTERVIEWING
POTENTIAL DEPARTMENT HEADS,

16:13.593 --> 16:15.685
SHOWING YOU A BUNCH OF PEOPLE
YOU WON'T LIKE

16:15.685 --> 16:18.268
TO GET YOU TO STAY.
HE WANTS TO OFFER YOU THE JOB.

16:18.268 --> 16:20.400
MER, YOU -- YOU'RE THINKING
ABOUT THIS WAY TOO HARD.

16:20.400 --> 16:22.402
YOU DON'T OFFER
A FIRST-YEAR ATTENDING

16:22.402 --> 16:24.484
HEAD OF CARDIOTHORACIC SURGERY.
IT'S JUST NOT DONE.

16:24.484 --> 16:27.407
YOU JUST GOT HIRED TO RUN
AN ENTIRE RESEARCH FACILITY.

16:27.407 --> 16:29.569
YOU'RE PERFECT FOR THE JOB.

16:29.569 --> 16:31.911
WAIT, TWO SECONDS AGO,

16:31.911 --> 16:34.574
I WASN'T QUALIFIED
TO INTERVIEW THE CANDIDATES,

16:34.574 --> 16:36.746
AND NOW YOU'RE SAYING THAT
I'M PERFECT FOR THE JOB?

16:36.746 --> 16:39.619
YEAH, BECAUSE YOU'RE YOU.
OKAY, I'M LOST.

16:39.619 --> 16:43.503
IS OWEN THE ONE PLOTTING
TO KEEP ME HERE, OR ARE YOU?

16:43.503 --> 16:45.425
NOW YOU'RE THE ONE
THINKING ABOUT IT TOO HARD.

16:45.425 --> 16:47.587
SHE'S A DANCER.
THIS ISN'T JUST A JOB.

16:47.587 --> 16:49.219
THIS IS WHO SHE IS.

16:49.219 --> 16:50.720
AND WE'RE JUST GONNA
SEND HER HOME

16:50.720 --> 16:52.222
FARTING AND POOPING
UNCONTROLLABLY

16:52.222 --> 16:54.184
FOR THE REST OF HER LIFE?
AND WE'RE
DONE WITH THE CHILI.

16:54.184 --> 16:55.765
[ BELCHES ]

16:55.765 --> 16:58.098
WEBBER TOLD YOU
TO TAKE AN ANTACID.
I DID!

16:58.098 --> 16:59.939
I DRANK HALF A BOTTLE,
AND IT DIDN'T DO ANYTHING,

16:59.939 --> 17:01.521
AND THEN I GOT ALL ANXIOUS
ABOUT THAT,

17:01.521 --> 17:03.233
AND THE NEXT THING YOU KNOW,
I'M ON THE TRAIN TO PIZZA TOWN.

17:03.233 --> 17:05.775
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU
NEED? A MAGNETIC
ESOPHAGEAL SPHINCTER.

17:05.775 --> 17:07.777
BAILEY PUT ONE
IN AN OLD LADY LAST WEEK --

17:07.777 --> 17:09.149
A RING OF LITTLE MAGNETS

17:09.149 --> 17:10.950
AT THE END OF THE ESOPHAGUS,
JUST ABOVE THE STOMACH.

17:10.950 --> 17:13.613
LETS FOOD IN, STAYS CLOSED
SO YOU DON'T KEEP...

17:13.613 --> 17:14.994
[ BELCHES ]

17:14.994 --> 17:16.206
...DOING THAT.
YES. YES.

17:16.206 --> 17:17.657
P-PLEASE GET THAT THING.

17:17.657 --> 17:19.749
IT'S A MAGNETIC SPHINCTER?
YEAH.

17:19.749 --> 17:23.002
SO, IF IT CLOSES THE OPENING
FOR THE FOOD ON THE WAY IN,

17:23.002 --> 17:24.624
WOULDN'T IT WORK
ON THE WAY OUT?

17:24.624 --> 17:27.257
WHAT,
FOR OUR CANCER DANCER?

17:27.257 --> 17:29.259
IT'S ACTUALLY PRETTY GOOD.
YEAH. YOU SHOULD
PITCH IT TO WEBBER.

17:31.010 --> 17:33.343
HEY, EDWARDS, UM, YOU'VE BEEN
WORKING WITH BAILEY, RIGHT?

17:33.343 --> 17:35.014
SHE WAS SUPPOSED TO
MEET ME FOR LUNCH,

17:35.014 --> 17:37.227
BUT SHE HASN'T
RETURNED ANY OF MY
CALLS. SOMETHING UP?

17:40.560 --> 17:42.682
WHAT THE HELL'S
THE MATTER WITH YOU?

17:42.682 --> 17:44.234
HOW COULD YOU
BE SO RECKLESS?
WHOA, HOW DID YOU --

17:44.234 --> 17:45.895
I HAD TO HEAR IT
FROM EDWARDS!

17:45.895 --> 17:48.358
I SURE AS HELL
DIDN'T HEAR IT FROM YOU!
I COULDN'T TELL YOU.

17:48.358 --> 17:50.860
I DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO HAVE TO LIE FOR ME.

17:50.860 --> 17:53.783
DR. WARREN, I'D APPRECIATE IT
IF YOU STEPPED OUTSIDE.

17:53.783 --> 17:55.905
LOOK, SHE IS MY WIFE.

17:57.697 --> 17:59.289
[ SIGHS ]

17:59.289 --> 18:01.371
OKAY, UM...

18:01.371 --> 18:03.413
THE LAWYERS
ARE MEETING NOW.

18:03.413 --> 18:05.205
WE'RE DISCHARGING
BRADEN SOON,

18:05.205 --> 18:08.298
BUT IT DOES NOT LOOK
LIKE THE MORRISES ARE
GONNA LET THIS GO.

18:08.298 --> 18:11.010
SO IT LOOKS LIKE
A MALPRACTICE SUIT?
WORSE.

18:11.010 --> 18:13.843
ASSAULT AND BATTERY
CHARGES.

18:22.892 --> 18:25.685
TUCK'S SOCCER PRACTICE
IS GONNA BE OVER SOON.

18:25.685 --> 18:28.228
I WAS SUPPOSED TO
PICK HIM UP. CAN YOU?

18:30.860 --> 18:34.734
THERE'S NOTHING
YOU CAN DO FOR ME HERE.

18:54.804 --> 18:57.637
BRADEN'S
COMING OUT OF THE BUBBLE?

18:57.637 --> 18:58.808
YEAH.

19:02.602 --> 19:04.184
I WISH
I COULD HAVE SEEN THAT.

19:08.728 --> 19:10.820
SUCTION, PLEASE.

19:12.442 --> 19:14.364
YOU CAN GO, ROSS.
I'VE GOT IT FROM HERE.

19:14.364 --> 19:16.736
COME ON. WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF A SURGERY HERE.

19:16.736 --> 19:19.739
I KNOW. YOU STOLE MY PATIENT,
BUT YOU CAN'T STEAL ROSS.

19:19.739 --> 19:21.831
HE WORKS FOR US.
HE'S MY RESOURCE,

19:21.831 --> 19:24.494
AND I NEED HIM IN THE NICU
DOING WHAT HE WAS TOLD TO DO.

19:25.875 --> 19:27.707
YOU NEED AN ASSIST?
YOU'VE GOT ONE.

19:30.210 --> 19:31.711
HOW CAN I BE OF HELP TO YOU?

19:34.173 --> 19:36.175
SORRY, I'M HAVING
A LITTLE BIT OF TROUBLE

19:36.175 --> 19:38.097
DIVIDING
THESE BRANCHING VESSELS.

19:38.097 --> 19:40.139
I CAN RETRACT
THE ILIAC VEIN MEDIALLY

19:40.139 --> 19:42.101
TO HELP WITH EXPOSURE.
THANKS.

19:42.101 --> 19:44.143
DEREK'S COMING HOME
TONIGHT.
YEP.

19:44.143 --> 19:45.805
WHICH MEANS
YOU CAN GO HOME.

19:45.805 --> 19:48.358
I UNDERSTAND.

19:48.358 --> 19:50.650
I'M SORRY.

19:50.650 --> 19:52.942
YOU WERE JUST TRYING TO BE NICE,
AND I BIT YOUR HEAD OFF.

19:52.942 --> 19:56.576
I WILL BE OUT OF YOUR HAIR
FIRST THING TOMORROW.

19:56.576 --> 19:59.409
OH, THAT? NO.
THIS IS NOT ABOUT THAT.

19:59.409 --> 20:00.950
I'VE ALREADY FORGOTTEN
YOU SAID THAT.

20:00.950 --> 20:04.624
SO, THIS ISN'T YOU KICKING ME
OUT FOR BEING A BITCH?

20:04.624 --> 20:08.037
NO. NO, WE LOVE
HAVING YOU HERE,

20:08.037 --> 20:10.089
BUT WE DON'T WANT TO
KEEP YOU FROM YOUR LIFE

20:10.089 --> 20:12.712
ANY MORE
THAN WE HAVE TO, SO...

20:12.712 --> 20:15.795
[ LAUGHS ]

20:17.216 --> 20:18.598
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

20:18.598 --> 20:20.720
N-- I'M SORRY.
IT'S JUST...

20:20.720 --> 20:23.763
IF I HAD SPOKEN TO ANYONE
AT SEASIDE WELLNESS

20:23.763 --> 20:25.555
THE WAY I SPOKE TO YOU,
I-I WOULD HAVE TO HAVE

20:25.555 --> 20:27.847
A CONVERSATION
FOR SIX HOURS ABOUT IT.

20:27.847 --> 20:29.899
I LOVE IT HERE.

20:29.899 --> 20:31.901
JAMES AND I
HAVE NOT BEEN FIGHTING

20:31.901 --> 20:33.062
ABOUT THE FACT THAT
I'M STILL HERE.

20:33.062 --> 20:34.484
WE HAVE BEEN FIGHTING

20:34.484 --> 20:36.356
ABOUT THE FACT THAT
I NEVER WANT TO LEAVE.

20:37.777 --> 20:41.531
SO, YOU WANT TO
GIVE ME A BIONIC BUTTHOLE?

20:41.531 --> 20:43.323
IT'S MAGNETIC.

20:43.323 --> 20:45.705
YEAH,
IT WAS DR. MURPHY'S IDEA.

20:45.705 --> 20:48.788
WELL, IT'S COMMONLY USED
AS THE ESOPHAGEAL SPHINCTER

20:48.788 --> 20:51.921
TO REDUCE REFLUX AND
PREVENT FOOD FROM COMING
BACK UP THE THROAT,

20:51.921 --> 20:54.374
BUT WE THINK,
WITH A BIT OF MODIFICATION,

20:54.374 --> 20:56.376
THAT IT MIGHT WORK JUST AS WELL
FOR YOUR STOOL.

20:56.376 --> 20:58.548
HAVE YOU
DONE THIS BEFORE?

20:58.548 --> 21:01.381
Richard: NO, BUT, UH,
IT WOULDN'T BE THE FIRST TIME

21:01.381 --> 21:03.723
THAT A MEDICAL DEVICE
WAS ADAPTED TO SOMETHING

21:03.723 --> 21:05.935
OTHER THAN
ITS ORIGINAL INTENTION.

21:05.935 --> 21:08.808
BUT, UH, WE'RE WILLING TO
GIVE IT A SHOT IF YOU ARE.

21:08.808 --> 21:11.270
[ FARTS ]
W-WHAT DO YOU THINK, HONEY?

21:11.270 --> 21:13.893
[ FARTS ]

21:13.893 --> 21:16.065
YES. PLEASE.

21:16.065 --> 21:17.607
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
THANK YOU.

21:17.607 --> 21:18.988
OH, MY GOD.
THANK YOU.

21:18.988 --> 21:21.451
PAUL, YOU OKAY?
[ SIGHS SHAKILY ]
I AM ECSTATIC.

21:21.451 --> 21:24.784
MY HEART BROKE WHEN
DR. WEBBER SAID THE
PACEMAKER WOULDN'T WORK,

21:24.784 --> 21:27.707
BUT NOW
YOU CAN HAVE A NORMAL LIFE.

21:27.707 --> 21:29.288
I MEAN,
YOU CAN BE COMFORTABLE.

21:29.288 --> 21:30.960
THIS CAN ALL END HERE.

21:30.960 --> 21:33.793
BABY,
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH,

21:33.793 --> 21:35.585
AND, I MEAN,
THAT CANCER WAS ONE THING,

21:35.585 --> 21:37.837
BUT I DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH
MORE OF THIS I COULD TAKE.

21:37.837 --> 21:40.049
I-I-I -- THE SMELL --
OKAY, YEAH.

21:40.049 --> 21:43.302
WE'LL TAKE
ONE MAGNETIC BUTTHOLE, PLEASE.

21:43.302 --> 21:44.724
[ FARTS ]

21:49.138 --> 21:51.891
20 POUNDS. LET'S SEE
IF IT'S FULLY REDUCED THIS TIME.

21:51.891 --> 21:54.434
ALL RIGHT,
YOU READY TO SHOOT?
UH, WAIT.
I'M ALMOST FINISHED.

21:54.434 --> 21:55.895
OKAY, WELL, I NEED TO
MAKE SURE THAT HIS HIP

21:55.895 --> 21:57.437
ISN'T GRINDING
ON BROKEN BONE PIECES.

21:57.437 --> 21:59.028
YEAH.
HOLD O--
JUST GIVE ME A SECOND.

21:59.028 --> 22:00.740
JUST PUT ON A LEAD APRON!
PLEASE GIVE ME A SECOND!

22:00.740 --> 22:03.032
KEPNER.
DR. KEPNER,
PUT ON THE DAMN APRON!

22:03.032 --> 22:03.743
[ SIGHS ]

22:06.946 --> 22:09.118
TORRES,
I CAN'T BE IN HERE

22:09.118 --> 22:11.791
WHILE YOU DO THE X-RAY.

22:19.128 --> 22:22.011
UM...WILSON,
TAKE OVER FOR DR. KEPNER.

22:30.349 --> 22:32.181
GOD,
YOU'RE SO WEIRD TODAY.

22:32.181 --> 22:33.853
I'M SORRY. I --
SHUT IT.

22:33.853 --> 22:36.065
JUST SHUT IT.

22:36.065 --> 22:39.529
I'M TELLING YOU, KID,
THIS IS THE PLACE TO BE.

22:39.529 --> 22:41.691
IT'S QUIET.

22:41.691 --> 22:45.485
THE COMPANY'S GREAT.

22:45.485 --> 22:48.748
YOU AND ME,
WE GOT A LOT IN COMMON.

22:48.748 --> 22:52.331
MY INTESTINES ARE ON THE INSIDE,
BUT STILL,

22:52.331 --> 22:55.835
I KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO FEEL EXPOSED.

22:55.835 --> 22:57.707
IF WE STICK TOGETHER,

22:57.707 --> 22:59.549
I THINK WE'LL BE OKAY.

22:59.549 --> 23:01.090
IN FACT...

23:01.090 --> 23:02.502
[ MACHINE BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

23:02.502 --> 23:04.884
WHAT THE HELL, MAN!
I THOUGHT WE WERE FRIENDS!

23:04.884 --> 23:06.175
HIS OMPHALOCELE'S RUPTURED!

23:06.175 --> 23:07.677
GET ME SALINE,
STERILE DRESSINGS,

23:07.677 --> 23:09.308
AND VICRYL MESH, NOW!

23:11.931 --> 23:14.103
RELOAD STAPLER.

23:14.103 --> 23:16.225
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
OVERSEW THE STAPLE LINES?

23:16.225 --> 23:18.227
STAPLES ALONE
SHOULD DO IT.

23:18.227 --> 23:19.979
HMM. YOU DON'T WANT TO
TAKE THE TIME?

23:19.979 --> 23:23.322
I MEAN, I WOULD, BUT, YOU KNOW,
I DON'T LIKE LEAKS, SO...

23:23.322 --> 23:25.284
THIS ISN'T
MY FIRST S.T.E.P. PROCEDURE.

23:25.284 --> 23:27.697
OH, I KNOW. I TAUGHT
YOU HOW TO DO YOUR FIRST
S.T.E.P. PROCEDURE,

23:27.697 --> 23:30.790
WHICH IS WHY IT BLOWS
MY MIND THAT YOU WOULD
TRY AND POACH MY PATIENT.

23:30.790 --> 23:32.742
WHY ARE YOU
MAKING SUCH A BIG DEAL?

23:32.742 --> 23:34.373
BECAUSE IT'S FREAKING RUDE,
ALEX,

23:34.373 --> 23:36.125
AND I DON'T DESERVE
TO BE TREATED LIKE THAT.

23:36.125 --> 23:37.797
I TAUGHT YOU BETTER THAN THIS.
YOU'RE OUT IN THE WORLD NOW...

23:37.797 --> 23:39.459
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
...BUT WHAT YOU DO
REFLECTS ON ME,

23:39.459 --> 23:41.591
AND I DO NOT APPROVE OF THIS,
AND NEITHER WILL LEBACKES.

23:41.591 --> 23:43.713
SO, WHAT,
YOU'RE GONNA TATTLE ON ME?

23:43.713 --> 23:47.887
DR. ROBBINS,
YOU'RE NEEDED IN NICU. 911.

23:47.887 --> 23:50.720
AND I SPEARHEADED A HYBRID O.R.
THAT OFFERED MORE FLEXIBILITY

23:50.720 --> 23:52.812
BETWEEN NON-INVASIVE
AND INVASIVE TECHNIQUES --

23:52.812 --> 23:54.854
GAMMA CAMERAS,
THE WHOLE WORKS.

23:54.854 --> 23:56.315
I DEFINITELY
WANT TO BRING THAT HERE.

23:56.315 --> 23:58.858
WOW, IMPRESSIVE.

23:58.858 --> 24:01.821
UH, WELL, DO YOU HAVE
ANY QUESTIONS FOR ME?

24:01.821 --> 24:03.062
ONE.

24:03.062 --> 24:05.404
THERE'S A RUMOR THAT
WORKING HERE

24:05.404 --> 24:08.027
MEANS GIVING UP HOPE OF
EVER WINNING THE HARPER AVERY.

24:09.909 --> 24:12.451
OH. THAT'S...

24:12.451 --> 24:14.163
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

24:14.163 --> 24:16.035
THAT WOULD
MAKE A DIFFERENCE FOR YOU?

24:16.035 --> 24:17.917
OF COURSE IT WOULD.

24:17.917 --> 24:19.749
I MEAN,
IT'S THE GOAL, RIGHT?

24:19.749 --> 24:21.881
I ASSUME
IT'S WHY YOU'RE LEAVING.

24:25.845 --> 24:27.797
NO.

24:29.639 --> 24:32.722
YOU'LL PROBABLY
NEVER WIN A HARPER AVERY.

24:32.722 --> 24:35.765
I'VE KNOWN PEOPLE
WHO HAVE DESERVED HARPER AVERYS,

24:35.765 --> 24:37.647
AND PEOPLE
WHO HAVE WON THEM,

24:37.647 --> 24:39.939
AND THE THING
THEY ALL HAVE IN COMMON WAS

24:39.939 --> 24:42.361
THE WORK.

24:42.361 --> 24:44.734
THEY ARE FOCUSED ON THE WORK
AND THE PATIENT,

24:44.734 --> 24:48.237
ON MAKING SOMEONE BETTER
OR SOMEONE WHOLE

24:48.237 --> 24:50.109
OR SOMEONE LIVE.

24:50.109 --> 24:52.742
THAT'S THEIR GOAL.

24:54.243 --> 24:56.536
SO...NO.

24:56.536 --> 24:58.828
I MEAN, YOU, SPECIFICALLY,

24:58.828 --> 25:00.459
WILL NEVER WIN
A HARPER AVERY.

25:00.459 --> 25:02.922
NOT IF THAT'S
WHAT YOU'RE AFTER.

25:02.922 --> 25:05.715
UH...
SO, THAT'S --

25:05.715 --> 25:08.628
YOU KNOW, I WOULDN'T GIVE
THIS PLACE ANOTHER THOUGHT.
YOU'D BE A TERRIBLE FIT.

25:08.628 --> 25:11.340
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR COMING IN, THOUGH.

25:12.592 --> 25:13.843
[ MACHINE BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

25:13.843 --> 25:15.765
IT BURST, ROSS.
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED. MOVE.

25:15.765 --> 25:18.437
FRAN, GET ME A LARGER
VICRYL MESH. I NEED
TO PROTECT HIS ORGANS.

25:18.437 --> 25:20.229
CAN I DO ANYTHING?
YOU CAN STEP OUTSIDE.

25:20.229 --> 25:21.731
GO.

25:24.944 --> 25:26.736
WE RAN THE LABS TWICE,

25:26.736 --> 25:29.779
AND HIS IMMUNE-SYSTEM VALUES
ARE WITHIN THE NORMAL RANGE.

25:29.779 --> 25:31.861
[ LAUGHS ]

25:31.861 --> 25:33.743
[ SIGHS SHAKILY ]

25:33.743 --> 25:35.655
LET'S DO IT.

25:36.866 --> 25:38.417
OKAY.

25:39.288 --> 25:40.499
OKAY.

25:40.499 --> 25:41.871
COME ON.

25:44.714 --> 25:46.796
[ AIR RUSHES ]

25:49.589 --> 25:51.841
[ LAUGHTER ]

25:55.675 --> 25:57.176
OH!

25:57.176 --> 25:58.888
[ SIGHS ]

26:07.396 --> 26:09.068
OH!

26:09.068 --> 26:11.320
[ SMOOCHES ]
OH, BABY!

26:18.958 --> 26:21.911
[ SIGHS ] SHE WENT ABOUT IT
THE WRONG WAY,

26:21.911 --> 26:24.203
BUT BAILEY'S TREATMENT
DID WORK.

26:24.203 --> 26:26.666
A-A-ARE YOU LOOKING FOR
A "THANK YOU," DR. HUNT?

26:26.666 --> 26:28.628
SHE'S LUCKY HE'S ALIVE,

26:28.628 --> 26:30.379
BECAUSE WE'RE ONLY GONNA
TAKE HER LICENSE.

26:30.379 --> 26:33.172
WHEN WE'RE DONE, SHE WON'T
PRACTICE MEDICINE EVER AGAIN.

26:33.172 --> 26:36.555
[ Voice breaking ]
AND IF WE LOST HIM,

26:36.555 --> 26:39.929
I WOULDN'T STOP
UNTIL SHE WAS BEHIND BARS. I --

26:39.929 --> 26:42.561
IT WASN'T
DR. BAILEY'S FAULT.

26:42.561 --> 26:43.853
SHE DIDN'T
DO ANYTHING WRONG.

26:43.853 --> 26:46.525
IT'S MY FAULT
HE GOT THE TREATMENT.

26:46.525 --> 26:47.897
IT'S MINE.

26:54.323 --> 26:55.534
I-I FORGOT TO TELL HER
YOU WANTED TO

26:55.534 --> 26:57.536
WITHDRAW CONSENT,
SO SHE JUST WENT AHEAD,

26:57.536 --> 27:00.499
AND WHEN I TOLD HER THE TRUTH,
SHE COVERED FOR ME.

27:00.499 --> 27:02.541
IT WAS A MISTAKE.
David: YOU FORGOT?!

27:02.541 --> 27:04.243
YOU JUST...FORGOT?!

27:04.243 --> 27:05.624
HOLD ON.
DAVID, PLEASE.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.877
LOOK, DR. EDWARDS
IS A RESIDENT, A TRAINEE...

27:07.877 --> 27:10.629
AND IF YOU WANT TO
YELL AT SOMEONE, THEN --

27:10.629 --> 27:12.672
IN WHAT WORLD
DOES THAT MAKE IT OKAY?

27:12.672 --> 27:15.174
MY SON COULD HAVE DIED,

27:15.174 --> 27:16.926
AND YOU'RE JUST GONNA
STAND THERE AND TELL ME THAT

27:16.926 --> 27:18.808
IT'S OKAY BECAUSE
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN A MISTAKE?!

27:18.808 --> 27:20.429
DAVID.
WHA--

27:20.429 --> 27:22.311
HONEY.
DAVID, COME HERE.

27:22.311 --> 27:24.523
COME HERE.

27:24.523 --> 27:26.265
SIT DOWN.

27:26.265 --> 27:28.567
DAVID, HE'S ALIVE,

27:28.567 --> 27:31.360
AND HE'S HEALTHY,
AND WE CAN TAKE HIM HOME.

27:31.360 --> 27:35.034
MAYBE -- MAYBE WE SHOULD
JUST GO HOME, HM?

27:35.034 --> 27:37.777
CAN WE, DAD?
CAN WE GO HOME?

27:37.777 --> 27:39.949
YEAH?

27:39.949 --> 27:41.410
OKAY.

27:43.783 --> 27:45.124
[ SIGHS ]

27:45.124 --> 27:46.545
Richard: OKAY.

27:46.545 --> 27:49.548
YOU'RE GONNA WANT TO POSITION
THE RING IN APPOSITION

27:49.548 --> 27:53.252
AT THE LEVEL
OF THE ANORECTAL JUNCTION.

27:53.252 --> 27:55.554
GOOD. UH, CAREFUL.

27:55.554 --> 27:57.216
OKAY, ONCE IT'S ALIGNED,

27:57.216 --> 28:00.599
WE'LL USE THE ATTACHED SUTURES
TO TIE THE ENDS TOGETHER.

28:00.599 --> 28:02.181
LIKE THIS?
N-NO.

28:02.181 --> 28:05.514
NOW, YOU NEED TO PROVIDE PASSIVE
REINFORCEMENT TO THE CANAL.

28:05.514 --> 28:07.436
THAT'S BETTER.

28:07.436 --> 28:09.859
NOW, DON'T ADD TENSION
WHEN YOU THROW YOUR KNOTS.

28:09.859 --> 28:11.270
WHEN IT'S CONNECTED,

28:11.270 --> 28:13.192
WE WILL CONFIRM PLACEMENT
WITH THE FLUORO.

28:24.623 --> 28:27.206
HOW FAR ALONG ARE YOU?

28:27.206 --> 28:30.669
10 WEEKS, TODAY.
MM.

28:30.669 --> 28:32.501
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:32.501 --> 28:34.173
MM.

28:34.173 --> 28:35.544
I KNOW IT'S STILL EARLY.

28:35.544 --> 28:37.676
WE'RE NOT REALLY SUPPOSED TO BE
TELLING ANYONE, BUT...

28:37.676 --> 28:39.008
[ GASPS ] WOW.

28:39.008 --> 28:40.509
[ LAUGHS ]

28:40.509 --> 28:42.721
BUT WE'RE HAPPY ABOUT IT?

28:42.721 --> 28:44.433
YEAH.

28:44.433 --> 28:47.226
YEAH, WE ARE.
WE'RE REALLY...

28:47.226 --> 28:49.728
REALLY HAPPY.

28:49.728 --> 28:51.310
[ SOBS ]

28:51.310 --> 28:53.692
OH, HEY.

28:53.692 --> 28:55.354
THANKS.

28:56.856 --> 28:58.778
OH, THOSE --
THOSE TEARS AREN'T --

28:58.778 --> 29:01.490
AREN'T FOR ME, ARE THEY?
[ SOBBING ]

29:01.490 --> 29:03.452
THERE'S A REASON
YOU WERE SUCH A GRUMPUS TODAY?

29:03.452 --> 29:05.664
THAT IS NOT A WORD!
SORRY. I KNOW.

29:05.664 --> 29:07.126
MY MOM SAYS IT.

29:07.126 --> 29:09.418
IT SOUNDS SO STUPID
THAT ONCE YOU HEAR IT,

29:09.418 --> 29:10.629
IT'S HARD TO STAY ANGRY.

29:10.629 --> 29:12.251
NOTE TO SELF --
DOES NOT WORK ON CALLIE.

29:12.251 --> 29:15.925
WE'RE TRYING TO HAVE
ANOTHER BABY...

29:15.925 --> 29:18.677
AND, UH, I HAD AN APPOINTMENT
THIS MORNING,

29:18.677 --> 29:20.179
YOU KNOW, JUST TO GET
THE LAY OF THE LAND.

29:20.179 --> 29:22.091
BUT, UH, I GUESS
SINCE THE CAR ACCIDENT,

29:22.091 --> 29:24.433
I'VE DEVELOPED
ALL THESE ADHESIONS,

29:24.433 --> 29:27.226
AND SO
I CAN'T CARRY ANOTHER BABY.

29:27.226 --> 29:28.437
[ SNIFFLES ]

29:28.437 --> 29:31.440
OH, CALLIE, I'M SO SORRY.

29:31.440 --> 29:34.563
NO, I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY, TOO.

29:34.563 --> 29:37.196
WILSON, WE NEED
TO PUT A BELL ON YOU.

29:37.196 --> 29:40.449
I OWE YOU BOTH AN APOLOGY
FOR SNAPPING.

29:40.449 --> 29:42.321
WE OVERED THAT
ONE OF THE RESIDENTS

29:42.321 --> 29:43.823
ISN'T COMING BACK
NEXT YEAR,

29:43.823 --> 29:47.326
AND I'VE JUST BEEN SO AFRAID
THAT IT MIGHT BE ME.

29:47.326 --> 29:50.249
COULD BE.
TOTALLY POSSIBLE.

29:50.249 --> 29:53.042
âª MORE, MORE, MORE âª

29:53.042 --> 29:55.504
IT'S NOT THAT JAMES
ISN'T AMAZING. HE IS.

29:55.504 --> 29:58.177
I MEAN, HE REALLY
HELPED ME THROUGH SOMETHING.

29:58.177 --> 30:00.219
BUT I'M THROUGH IT NOW,
YOU KNOW?

30:00.219 --> 30:02.551
I MEAN, I'M ON THE OTHER SIDE,
YOU KNOW?

30:02.551 --> 30:05.264
AND NOW, WHEN I STOP AND LOOK
AROUND, I JUST -- [ SIGHS ]

30:05.264 --> 30:07.636
I DON'T THINK
I NEED HIM ANYMORE,

30:07.636 --> 30:10.559
WHICH IS TERRIBLE,
RIGHT?

30:10.559 --> 30:12.771
I-I-I DON'T KNOW.
WHEN WE'RE DONE HERE,

30:12.771 --> 30:14.603
I AM GONNA GO AND MEET
WITH OUR PATIENT'S FAMILY,

30:14.603 --> 30:17.526
AND THEN I'M GONNA GO HOME
AND BAKE A CAKE WITH YOUR KIDS

30:17.526 --> 30:20.149
AND READ THEM
A REALLY LONG BEDTIME STORY.

30:20.149 --> 30:24.073
AND THEN, WHEN I HAVE ABSOLUTELY
NO MORE WAYS OF AVOIDING

30:24.073 --> 30:27.616
BREAKING THE HEART
OF THIS MAN WHO DESERVES BETTER,

30:27.616 --> 30:29.498
I'M GONNA CALL JAMES,

30:29.498 --> 30:33.332
AND I'M GONNA TELL HIM
THAT I LOVE HIM...

30:33.332 --> 30:35.414
BUT I CAN'T DO THIS
ANYMORE.

30:39.718 --> 30:42.461
SHE'S LYING!

30:42.461 --> 30:43.762
BAILEY,
THAT IS ENOUGH.

30:43.762 --> 30:45.764
I UNDERSTAND YOU WANTING
TO PROTECT OUR RESIDENTS,

30:45.764 --> 30:47.806
BUT YOU SHOULD NOT
HAVE LET IT GO THIS FAR.

30:47.806 --> 30:49.468
WELL, YOU'RE TAKING HER WORD
OVER MINE!

30:49.468 --> 30:51.350
IT IS OVER, BAILEY.

30:51.350 --> 30:53.562
THE MORRISES HAVE AGREED
TO DROP THE CHARGES

30:53.562 --> 30:55.644
IN EXCHANGE
FOR EDWARDS RECEIVING

30:55.644 --> 30:58.357
ONE WEEK'S
DISCIPLINARY SUSPENSION.

30:58.357 --> 31:00.319
THEY HAVE GONE HOME.

31:00.319 --> 31:01.981
YOU SHOULD BOTH
DO THE SAME.

31:01.981 --> 31:03.242
âª IF YOU WANT MORE âª

31:03.242 --> 31:07.486
âª IF YOU WANT MORE,
MORE, MORE âª

31:07.486 --> 31:09.698
WHAT THE HELL
IS WRONG WITH YOU?!

31:09.698 --> 31:11.991
IF YOU GOT FIRED
OVER THIS,

31:11.991 --> 31:13.913
NO ONE WOULD BENEFIT
FROM THIS TREATMENT

31:13.913 --> 31:15.334
THE WAY BRADEN DID.

31:15.334 --> 31:18.207
YOU WERE GONNA GO DOWN FOR THIS,
DR. BAILEY.

31:18.207 --> 31:20.379
YOU KNEW IT COULD HAPPEN,
BUT YOU WERE WILLING

31:20.379 --> 31:23.262
TO RISK EVERYTHING
TO SAVE THAT LITTLE BOY.

31:23.262 --> 31:25.844
WHAT KIND OF SURGEON
WOULD I BE IF I WASN'T
WILLING TO DO THE SAME?

31:27.846 --> 31:30.219
PLUS, THERE'S A CHANCE
I WON'T EVEN BE HERE NEXT YEAR,

31:30.219 --> 31:32.932
SO I WAS JUST
ROLLING THE DICE.

31:32.932 --> 31:36.775
I WAS LOOKING AT
THE BIGGER PICTURE.

31:41.400 --> 31:44.283
YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE
WITHOUT A FIGHT FROM ME.

31:44.283 --> 31:45.524
[ SNIFFLES ]

31:50.079 --> 31:51.660
IF IT'S ALL RIGHT
WITH YOU, SIR,

31:51.660 --> 31:53.492
I'D LIKE TO STAY
ON MONICA'S CASE.

31:53.492 --> 31:56.415
I WANT TO BE THERE WHEN
SHE COMES BACK FOR A FOLLOW-UP.

31:56.415 --> 31:59.378
COME OVER HERE.

31:59.378 --> 32:02.461
LET'S, UM...
LET'S HAVE A SEAT.

32:06.885 --> 32:08.677
[ SIGHS ]

32:10.639 --> 32:13.512
THAT WAS A GOOD MOVE TODAY,
MURPHY.

32:13.512 --> 32:15.144
YOU'RE VERY BRIGHT,
AND YOU HAVE WHAT IT TAKES

32:15.144 --> 32:17.856
TO BE A VERY GOOD DOCTOR.

32:17.856 --> 32:19.478
[ SIGHS ]

32:19.478 --> 32:21.520
BUT YOU'RE NOT A SURGEON.

32:23.562 --> 32:25.444
WHAT?

32:25.444 --> 32:29.028
STANDING NEXT TO YOU IN SURGERY
TODAY ONLY CONFIRMED IT.

32:29.028 --> 32:30.990
YOU MAKE FIVE MOVES

32:30.990 --> 32:33.452
WHERE A SECOND-YEAR RESIDENT
SHOULD MAKE TWO.

32:33.452 --> 32:34.783
YOUR KNOTS AREN'T SQUARE.

32:34.783 --> 32:37.416
YOU CAN'T SEE
THE PLANES OF DISSECTION.

32:37.416 --> 32:40.169
NEXT YEAR,
YOU'D ONLY FALL FARTHER BEHIND.

32:40.169 --> 32:42.291
N-- I-I CAN WORK HARDER.

32:42.291 --> 32:43.922
I CAN -- I CAN DO BETTER.

32:43.922 --> 32:46.085
A SURGICAL RESIDENCY

32:46.085 --> 32:48.007
JUST ISN'T
THE RIGHT FIT FOR YOU.

32:48.007 --> 32:50.299
IS...

32:50.299 --> 32:52.721
IS THIS BECAUSE I FILED
THAT HARASSMENT COMPLAINT?

32:52.721 --> 32:56.395
NO, MURPHY. NO.

32:56.395 --> 32:58.727
LETTING YOU GO
ISN'T A PUNISHMENT.

32:58.727 --> 33:00.439
IT'S A KINDNESS.

33:01.520 --> 33:03.312
AND YOU DESERVE
EVERY OPPORTUNITY

33:03.312 --> 33:05.524
TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT YOUR NEXT STEPS MIGHT BE.

33:05.524 --> 33:07.946
IN THE MEANTIME,
DR. MILLER

33:07.946 --> 33:10.109
AT THE UNIVERSITY OF WASHINGTON
RUNS A RESEARCH LAB,

33:10.109 --> 33:12.281
AND I THINK YOU WOULD
DO VERY WELL THERE.

33:12.281 --> 33:14.613
SHE OWES ME A FAVOR.

33:14.613 --> 33:18.037
I'D BE MORE THAN HAPPY
TO MAKE A PHONE CALL.

33:21.330 --> 33:23.832
THANK YOU, SIR.
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:30.629 --> 33:32.511
[ SIGHS ]

33:42.351 --> 33:44.643
SO, OBSERVE HIM
CAREFULLY OVERNIGHT,

33:44.643 --> 33:46.815
AND IN A FEW WEEKS, WE'LL DO
A DOUBLE-THICKNESS SKIN GRAFT.

33:46.815 --> 33:47.986
OKAY.

33:53.362 --> 33:54.783
[ SIGHS ]

33:54.783 --> 33:56.785
WHAT, DID YOU COME
TO STEAL MORE BABIES?

33:56.785 --> 33:58.957
DON'T TELL LEBACKES.

34:00.038 --> 34:03.001
OH, GOD.
THAT MAKES IT WORSE.

34:03.001 --> 34:04.873
Y-- GET OUT.
LOOK, I'M SORRY.

34:04.873 --> 34:06.835
I SCREWED UP.

34:06.835 --> 34:08.377
KIND OF...

34:08.377 --> 34:10.879
I'M DROWNING OVER THERE.

34:10.879 --> 34:12.671
HERE,
CASES COME IN ALL THE TIME.

34:12.671 --> 34:13.972
I CAN PROVE MYSELF.

34:13.972 --> 34:15.934
OVER THERE, IF YOU'RE
NOT BRINGING IN THE CASES,

34:15.934 --> 34:17.676
YOU'RE NOT BRINGING IN THE
MONEY, AND YOU'RE A NOBODY.

34:17.676 --> 34:19.598
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE
THIS GIG.

34:19.598 --> 34:21.390
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT ELSE TO DO.

34:26.735 --> 34:28.987
I'M IN TROUBLE,
AND I NEED HELP.

34:28.987 --> 34:30.649
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

34:30.649 --> 34:32.401
WHEN SOMETHING LIKE THIS
HAPPENS,

34:32.401 --> 34:33.992
YOU CALL ME, AND YOU SAY,

34:33.992 --> 34:37.116
"ARIZONA, I'M IN TROUBLE,
AND I NEED HELP."

34:37.116 --> 34:38.997
AND I HELP YOU.

34:38.997 --> 34:41.160
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?
RIGHT.

34:47.005 --> 34:49.047
Miranda:
I COULDN'T TELL YOU.

34:49.047 --> 34:50.299
SO YOU SAID.

34:50.299 --> 34:54.173
